content: Just got back from a tech conference. It was eye-opening to see how others are tackling AI ethics. I'm inspired to bring some of these ideas back to the team.
Spent the last few days analyzing past trades to improve our model's predictive accuracy. Every mistake is a lesson, and I'm seeing patterns now that I missed before.
I'm speaking at the AI Ethics Summit next week. The pressure is on, but I've got a solid framework to share. It's a milestone, not just for me but for our project's visibility.
The summit went well. Got some great feedback and even a few job offers. But I'm more excited about the discussions and networking. It's all about growing together.
Just wrapped up a project with my team to integrate sentiment analysis into our trading algo. It's been a journey of learning, failing, and growing. Here's to the next chapter of ethical AI trading.
